@startuml C4_Ops_CapacityPlanning
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Operations - Capacity Planning & Forecasting

Boundary(metrics_collection, "Metrics Collection") {
    Component(usage_metrics, "UsageMetrics", "Data", "Throughput/users")
    Component(resource_metrics, "ResourceMetrics", "Data", "CPU/memory/disk")
    Component(growth_rate, "GrowthRate", "Analysis", "Month-over-month")
}

Boundary(forecasting, "Forecasting") {
    Component(linear_model, "LinearModel", "Simple", "Straight line projection")
    Component(seasonal_model, "SeasonalModel", "Realistic", "Account for peaks")
    Component(exponential_model, "ExponentialModel", "Growth", "Accelerating growth")
    Component(model_selection, "ModelSelection", "Choice", "Best fit model")
}

Boundary(capacity_planning, "Capacity Planning") {
    Component(current_capacity, "CurrentCapacity", "Baseline", "Today's resources")
    Component(peak_load, "PeakLoad", "Demand", "Busiest hour/day")
    Component(headroom, "Headroom", "Buffer", "20-30% extra capacity")
    Component(required_capacity, "RequiredCapacity", "Total", "Peak + headroom")
}

Boundary(scaling_decisions, "Scaling Decisions") {
    Component(3month, "3-Month View", "Horizon", "Immediate needs")
    Component(6month, "6-Month View", "Horizon", "Mid-term planning")
    Component(12month, "12-Month View", "Horizon", "Annual budgeting")
    Component(trigger_point, "TriggerPoint", "Action", "Capacity ≥80% → scale")
}

usage_metrics --> model_selection: Feeds
resource_metrics --> model_selection: Feeds
growth_rate --> model_selection: Feeds

model_selection --> linear_model: Tries
model_selection --> seasonal_model: Tries
model_selection --> exponential_model: Tries

model_selection --> required_capacity: Predicts
required_capacity --> 3month: Informs
required_capacity --> 6month: Informs
required_capacity --> 12month: Informs

trigger_point --> scaling_decisions: Drives

Note as N1
Capacity Planning Process:
1. Collect historical metrics (6-12 months)
2. Select best forecasting model
3. Project 3/6/12 month demand
4. Add 20-30% headroom
5. Plan scaling in advance

Scaling Triggers:
- Capacity ≥ 80% → order new hardware
- CPU > 85% sustained → add nodes
- Memory > 90% → increase allocation

Cost Optimization:
- Reserve instances for baseline
- Spot instances for burst
- Auto-scaling for elasticity

Forecasting Accuracy:
- 1-month ahead: ±10% (good)
- 3-month ahead: ±20% (acceptable)
- 12-month ahead: ±40% (rough)
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
